import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';
---
<BlogPostLayout
  title="How to play as Sgt. Forge - Halo Wars 2"
  description="Master Sergeant Forge in Halo Wars 2 with this guide covering Rolling Economy, the powerful Grizzly tanks, Combat Salvage, and the devastating Grizzly Battalion drop."
  category="Guides"
  publishedDate="Published on January 31, 2026"
  dateIso="2026-01-31"
  ogImage="/img/HW-Guides/Forge.jpg"
  youtubeId="7j09kRQ3zsM"
  tags={['Halo Wars 2']}
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    This guide covers Sergeant Forge, a UNSC leader. Forge is a free DLC leader, so there's no reason not to have him. He was the first new leader added to the game, and his design is heavily inspired by how he operated in Halo Wars 1. His unique unit is the Grizzly tank.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">Pros (Strengths)</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Cheaper Upgrades</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>First leader point (Rolling Economy) reduces supply pad and generator upgrade costs</li>
    <li>Faster economy means faster units, faster pushes, faster tech, or faster hero</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Forge Hog Hero</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Has an area buff around him that enhances nearby units</li>
    <li>Great Y ability: Scatterbomb (dubbed the "Lag Bomb")</li>
    <li>Scatterbomb slows enemy units trying to leave the area, causing massive damage</li>
    <li>Even better when upgraded at level 2</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Strong Vehicle Powers</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Accelerated Assembly</strong>: Reduces vehicle cost and training time</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Combat Salvage</strong>: First 8-10 vehicles lost automatically respawn at base</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Heavy Metal</strong>: Greatly increases vehicle defense</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Restoration Drones</strong>: Heals</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Pelican Transport</strong>: Unit mobility</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Veteran Kodiak Drop</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Can be upgraded for even more powerful Kodiaks</li>
    <li>Kodiaks arrive in Gunships that attack during the drop</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Grizzly Battalion</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>One of the strongest UNSC drops</li>
    <li>Drops 3 Vet 1 Grizzlies with Gunships</li>
    <li>Gunships attack while dropping the Grizzlies</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Grizzly Tanks</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Ton of hit points</li>
    <li>One of the strongest units in the game</li>
    <li>Up there with Colossus for strongest UNSC vehicle</li>
    <li>Good against everything except air</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Cons (Weaknesses)</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Expensive Grizzlies</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Even with Accelerated Assembly 1 and 2, Grizzlies are pricey</li>
    <li>Long training time (41-42 seconds each)</li>
    <li>High population cost (10 pop each vs Scorpion's 7)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">One-Dimensional</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Not as bad as Johnson, but predictable</li>
    <li>Opponents expect Grizzlies when they see Forge</li>
    <li>Can do Air Spam or Vulture Spam with Combat Salvage/Heavy Metal</li>
    <li>Can also do Pelican Rush with Flamethrowers early game</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Slow Units</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Grizzlies perform poorly on smaller maps</li>
    <li>Need Pelican Transport on larger maps</li>
    <li>Forge doesn't really thrive until Tech 3</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Build Orders</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Hero Opener (Recommended)</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">The Forge Hog is excellent early game - great against infantry.</p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Building Order:</strong>
  </p>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li>Generator (to get hero faster)</li>
    <li>Supply Pad</li>
    <li>Supply Pad</li>
    <li>Generator</li>
    <li>Armory (dubbed "The Build")</li>
  </ol>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Leader Points:</strong>
  </p>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Rolling Economy</strong> - Cheaper supply pad and generator upgrades</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Rolling Economy 2</strong> or <strong class="text-cyan-400">Heavy Metal</strong> (for Hero Opener)</li>
  </ol>

  <p class="mb-4">
    Once Forge Hog is out, get <strong class="text-cyan-400">Anvil Round</strong> upgrade - it's what makes Forge so good early. Note: Anvil Round cannot attack air but devastates infantry and does solid damage to vehicles.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Barracks Opener (Alternative)</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">For Flamethrowers, Snipers, and Marines early:</p>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li>Supply Pad</li>
    <li>Barracks (instead of Generator)</li>
    <li>Barracks</li>
    <li>Mini Base with Supply Pad</li>
    <li>Consider <strong class="text-cyan-400">Pelican</strong> at second leader point for the "Cheese" play (drop Flamethrowers behind enemy main base)</li>
  </ol>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Tech 2 Progression</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Forge Hog Upgrades:</strong> Defensive Aura upgrade makes Forge Hog even better
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Leader Points:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Scatterbomb</strong> - Recommended</li>
    <li>Then <strong class="text-cyan-400">Accelerated Assembly</strong> - Cheaper, faster vehicles</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Buildings:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Two Garages for Warthog production</li>
    <li>Accelerated Assembly benefits Warthogs now and Grizzlies at Tech 3</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Tech 3: Grizzly Time</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Grizzly Stats</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>850 supplies, 140 power (without Accelerated Assembly)</li>
    <li>760 supplies with Accelerated Assembly</li>
    <li>42 seconds to train (38 with Accelerated Assembly)</li>
    <li>Good against everything except air</li>
    <li>Very slow moving</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Essential Upgrades</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Advanced Logistics</strong> - Faster training</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Missile Barrage</strong> (1000 power) - Great for attacking bases, but expensive</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Vehicle Upgrades</strong> - Half the cost of Missile Barrage, increases damage and health</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Supporting Your Grizzlies</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Nightingales are essential:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Detect cloaked units (Banished cloaking generators)</li>
    <li>Heal in combat</li>
    <li>Y ability cloaks Grizzlies in emergencies</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Keep Forge Hog nearby</strong> - Grizzlies benefit from the aura buff
  </p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Don't go too heavy on Grizzlies:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>10 pop each limits other unit production</li>
    <li>Sprinkle in Wolverines for anti-air</li>
    <li>Support with Warthogs or infantry</li>
    <li>Grizzlies are NOT good against air</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Grizzly Battalion Drop</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Ultimate Ability:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Drops 3 Vet 1 Grizzlies</li>
    <li>Gunships provide temporary air support during the drop</li>
    <li>Can drop right in front of enemy base</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Warning:</strong> Watch out for <strong class="text-cyan-400">Jerome</strong>. He can drop Omega Team (3 Spartans) and hijack all three Grizzlies, giving him three Spartan Grizzlies.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Key Leader Points Path</h2>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Rolling Economy</strong> (first point always)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Rolling Economy 2</strong> or <strong class="text-cyan-400">Pelican</strong> (depending on build)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Scatterbomb</strong></li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Accelerated Assembly</strong></li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Combat Salvage</strong> or <strong class="text-cyan-400">Heavy Metal</strong></li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Grizzly Battalion</strong></li>
  </ol>

  <p class="mb-4">Other useful picks: Restoration Drones, Vehicle Drop (Kodiaks)</p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Summary</h2>

  <p class="mb-4">Forge is one of the easier leaders to play - not that complicated and quite fun. His play style isn't drastically different from standard UNSC gameplay.</p>

  <p class="mb-4">
    <strong class="text-cyan-400">Key Tips:</strong>
  </p>
  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li>Get Rolling Economy first - always</li>
    <li>Forge Hog with Anvil Round dominates early infantry</li>
    <li>Use Accelerated Assembly to reduce Grizzly costs</li>
    <li>Don't mass only Grizzlies - support with Wolverines and Nightingales</li>
    <li>Watch for Jerome's Omega Team when using Grizzly Battalion</li>
    <li>Consider Combat Salvage and Heavy Metal for vehicle protection</li>
    <li>Pelican Transport is essential on large maps due to Grizzly speed</li>
  </ol>
</BlogPostLayout>
